  "text": "The Kubernetes API deprecation policy is enforced through several key components in the API server:\n\n1. **Deprecation Warning Injection** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go):\n   - `IsDeprecated()` function checks if an API object implements the APILifecycleDeprecated interface and compares the deprecation version with the current server version\n   - `WarningMessage()` function generates human-readable deprecation warnings that include the deprecation version, removal version (if applicable), and replacement API (if available)\n   - `RemovedRelease()` function extracts the removal version from objects that implement APILifecycleRemoved interface\n\n2. **Removal Version Validation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/deleted_kinds.go):\n   - `RemoveDeletedKinds()` method removes API kinds and versions that have reached their removal date based on APILifecycleRemoved() versions\n   - `ShouldServeForVersion()` method determines if a resource should be served based on the removal version and current API server version\n   - Also checks APILifecycleIntroduced() to ensure a version isn't served before it was introduced\n   - Supports environment variables (KUBE_APISERVER_STRICT_REMOVED_API_HANDLING_IN_ALPHA, KUBE_APISERVER_SERVE_REMOVED_APIS_FOR_ONE_RELEASE) for controlling removal behavior\n\n3. **Minimum Supported API Version Checks** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go):\n   - `emulatedStorageVersion()` function selects the appropriate storage encoding version based on the minimum compatibility version\n   - Skips API versions that were introduced after the minimum compatibility version (using APILifecycleIntroduced())\n   - Used during the storage factory configuration to ensure compatibility with older client versions\n\n4. **Warning Handler Integration** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/warning/warning.go):\n   - `AddWarningsHandler()` wraps route handlers to inject deprecation warnings into HTTP responses via the Warning header\n\n5. **Metrics Tracking** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go):\n   - Tracks deprecated API requests through metrics (requested_deprecated_apis gauge)\n   - Adds audit annotations to flag deprecated API usage\n   - Instruments route functions with deprecated flag and removal release information\n\n6. **API Installation Flow** (pkg/controlplane/apiserver/apis.go):\n   - During API server startup, `InstallAPIs()` creates a ResourceExpirationEvaluator based on the current Kubernetes version\n   - Calls `RemoveDeletedKinds()` before installing any API groups to filter out removed APIs\n   - Only installs API groups and versions that should be served in the current Kubernetes version\n\n7. **Route Installation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go):\n   - For each API resource, checks if it's deprecated using `IsDeprecated()` \n   - Extracts the removal release using `RemovedRelease()`\n   - Generates warning messages using `WarningMessage()`\n   - Wraps all route handlers with `AddWarningsHandler()` to inject warnings into responses\n   - Passes deprecation and removal information to `InstrumentRouteFunc()` for metrics tracking\n\nThe enforcement chain ensures that:\n- APIs with removal dates in the past are not served at all\n- APIs currently marked as deprecated generate warnings in all responses\n- Clients are informed about which versions will be unavailable and what replacements to use\n- Metrics and audit logs track deprecated API usage for cluster administrators to monitor migration progress"
}

